---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 sm:py-20">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <span class="text-xs tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-seal-dark font-medium">About</span>
      <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl mt-4">SiteAge.org</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-ink-muted font-light leading-relaxed">
      <p class="text-lg">
        SiteAge.org is a website age certification platform. We trace the origins of websites
        using the Internet Archive's Wayback Machine and generate verifiable age badges.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4">How It Works</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3">
          <li>Enter a domain name to look up</li>
          <li>We query the Wayback Machine CDX API for the earliest archived snapshot</li>
          <li>The earliest successful snapshot date becomes the "birth date"</li>
          <li>You receive a certificate page and an embeddable SVG badge</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4">Verification</h2>
        <p>
          Website owners can claim their domain through DNS TXT record or meta tag verification.
          Verified domains receive a gold "Established" badge and can submit evidence for an
          earlier birth date if the Wayback Machine didn't capture the earliest version.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4">Open Source</h2>
        <p>
          SiteAge.org is open source under the MIT license.
          <a href="https://github.com/user/siteage.org" class="text-azure hover:text-azure-light transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            View on GitHub
          </a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
